-- Berkshire’s Witmer Buys Shares After Joining Buffett’s Board
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2013-05-24T20:21:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-24/berkshire-s-witmer-buys-shares-after-joining-buffett-s-board.html
Meryl Witmer, the newest director at
 Warren Buffett ’s Berkshire Hathaway Inc., acquired more than $1
million in the company’s stock after joining the board this
month.  Witmer, a general partner at Eagle Capital, added seven
Class A shares of Omaha, Nebraska-based Berkshire today and
yesterday for prices from $165,173 to $165,262.65, she said in a
regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
